    <entry>
      <title>Linux command</title>
      <link href="/2023/03/13/Linux-command/"/>
      <url>/2023/03/13/Linux-command/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="Introduction"><a href="#Introduction" class="headerlink" title="Introduction"></a>Introduction</h2><p>Here marks several linux commands.</p><h2 id="Commands"><a href="#Commands" class="headerlink" title="Commands"></a>Commands</h2><h3 id="1-pwd-command"><a href="#1-pwd-command" class="headerlink" title="1. pwd command"></a>1. pwd command</h3><p>The pwd command (print working directory) is a shell builtin command that prints the current location. The output shows an absolute directory path, starting with the root directory (&#x2F;).</p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">pwd &lt;options&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>The output prints the current location in the &#x2F;home&#x2F;<username> format.</p><h3 id="2-ls-command"><a href="#2-ls-command" class="headerlink" title="2. ls command"></a>2. ls command</h3><p>The ls command (list) prints a list of the current directory’s contents. Run the following:</p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">ls</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Additional options provide flexibility with the display output. Typical usage includes combining the following options:</p><ul><li>Show as a list:<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">ls -l</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li>Show as a list and include hidden files:<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">ls -la</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li>Show sizes in a human-readable format:<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">ls -lah</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ul>]]></content>
      
      
      <categories>
          
          <category> Learning </category>
          
      </categories>
      
      
